<i>adverb</i>: 확연히 [화견히], 확실히 [확씰히], 엄연히 [엄연히], 어련히 [어련히], 어김없이 [어기멉씨], 똑똑히 [똑또키], 두말없이 [두ː마럽씨], 극명히 [긍명히] <i>interjection</i>: 정말 [정ː말] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>확연히 [화견히]</dt><br>
<dd>clearly; definitely; obviously</dd><br>
<dd>아주 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Very clearly.</dd><br>
<dt>확실히 [확씰히]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; confidently; definitely</dd><br>
<dd>실제와 꼭 같거나 틀림없이 그러하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of being absolutely true or being certain of something.</dd><br>
<dt>엄연히 [엄연히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. composedly; refinedly</dd><br>
<dd>사람의 외모나 말, 행동 등이 침착하고 점잖게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a calm and gentle manner in one's appearance, speech, behavior, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. undeniably; clearly; definitely</dd><br>
<dd>누구도 부인할 수 없을 정도로 명백하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being so obvious as to be beyond dispute.</dd><br>
<dt>어련히 [어련히]</dt><br>
<dd>definitely; certainly; absolutely</dd><br>
<dd>걱정하지 않아도 될 만큼 잘될 것이 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a definite manner in which there is no need to worry because things will turn out fine.</dd><br>
<dt>어김없이 [어기멉씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. infallibly; punctually</dd><br>
<dd>약속 등을 어기는 일이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a way that one does not break a promise, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. unerringly; definitely</dd><br>
<dd>틀림이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a definite way with no doubt.</dd><br>
<dt>똑똑히 [똑또키]</dt><br>
<dd>1. definitely; explicitly</dd><br>
<dd>분명하고 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Clearly and distinctly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. cleverly; sensibly</dd><br>
<dd>머리가 좋고 영리하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Intelligently and wisely.</dd><br>
<dt>두말없이 [두ː마럽씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. without complaint</dd><br>
<dd>이런저런 불평을 하거나 덧붙이는 말이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any complaint or additional comment.</dd><br>
<dd>2. definitely; certainly</dd><br>
<dd>더 말할 필요도 없이 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Definitely without having to say anything further.</dd><br>
<dt>극명히 [긍명히]</dt><br>
<dd>definitely; obviously; distinctly</dd><br>
<dd>매우 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Very clearly.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>interjection</i><br>
<dt>정말 [정ː말]</dt><br>
<dd>1. oh no; darn it</dd><br>
<dd>놀랍거나 어떤 일을 심각하게 생각할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when one is surprised or thinks of a matter as being serious.</dd><br>
<dd>2. definitely; for sure</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 하겠다는 의지를 강조할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when one emphasizes his/her will to do something.</dd><br>
<dd>3. darn it; damn</dd><br>
<dd>화가 나거나 기가 막힘을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation that expresses anger or dumbfoundedness.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>